The National Energy Regulator of South Africa (Nersa) will hold virtual public hearings on State-owned power utility Eskom’s third Multi-Year Price Determination (MYPD3) Regulatory Clearing Account (RCA) Year 2 (2014/15), Year 3 (2015/16) and Year 4 (2016/17) applications, Eskom’s supplementary application and the implementation plan for the liquidation of the 2018/19 RCA balance. The hearings will be held on November 5 on Microsoft Teams. The public hearings for the three RCAs and the supplementary application will be held concurrently for each province from November 16. Those interested in attending or submitting comments must email publichearings@nersa.org.za. All public hearings will be live streamed on Nersa’s social media platforms.